  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was just-- I, I suppose he was not only a good obstetrician, but the clinic was probably set up nicer than having a midwife come to the house or going to a public hospital.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother generally helped my father when he was very busy with patients or preparing them, but then was-- the main occupation was simply being a mother and supervise the household.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it-- it actually started for us, for me, in 1938 when Czechoslovakia mobilized in late summer because of the threat of war from Hitler's Germany.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were evacuated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother and I were evacuated to the center of Bohemia, because our town was right on the German bor-- border with Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The, the frontier was maybe five kilometers or less from our house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at-- all during 1937 and '38, Czechoslovakia built a very strong defense line-- this was called the Second Maginot Line-- on its borders to be able to defend itself.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So when, when mobilization was declared, my father, who was a physician, stayed behind.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went to a cousin of ours in a, in a little-- in a smaller town where I went to a school with more kind of country kids.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that's where I learned how to stand on my head, which I can still do today.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe so, even though I was seven and then eight years old.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- you know, we were-- even there, we were digging air raid shelters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it, it was a pretty grim situation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was personally not aware that this was particularly dangerous for Jew-- for us Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
